title: UPDATE: 29-year-old girl killed in crash on Thompson Road
content: 05:15 PM EDT   Copyright 2018 Nexstar Broadcasting, Inc. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.   DEWITT, N.Y. (WSYR-TV) - One person is dead after a crash on Thompson Road in DeWitt.   Dewitt Police say they were called to a head on crash around 6:45 Saturday morning near Alden Avenue in Dewitt.   Officers say the driver of a Pontiac Grand Prix was heading south when they crossed the center line and hit a GMC Savana van heading north.   The driver of the Pontiac, 29-year-old Michelle Manos and passenger, 34-year-old James Caesar had to be extricated from the vehicle by rescue personnel.   They were both taken to Upstate Medical University. Manos died there as a result of her injuries. Caesar remains at the hospital with severe injuries.   The driver of the van, Jeffrey Schell, and passenger Paul Armstrong, were taken to Crouse Hospital for treatment. They've since been released.   The cause of the crash is still under investigation.
